import StaticPage from '@layouts/StaticPage.astro';
const updated = 'April 2026';
---

<StaticPage
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How ChevyRoots collects, uses, and protects your information. Independent Chevrolet resource — operated by Crystal."
  eyebrow="Legal"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
>
  <p><strong>Last updated: {updated}</strong></p>

  <p>ChevyRoots ("we," "us," "our") is an independent Chevrolet enthusiast website. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect when you visit chevyroots.com, why we collect it, and how we protect it.</p>

  <h2>What We Collect</h2>

  <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
  <p>When you subscribe to our newsletter, submit a build, contact us, or leave a review, you give us information voluntarily: email address, name, optional phone number, photos, and whatever else you type into the form. We use it only for the purpose you provided it for.</p>

  <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
  <p>Our analytics provider (Plausible Analytics) records anonymous, aggregate page views. Plausible does not use cookies, does not track users across websites, and does not collect personally identifiable information. We chose Plausible specifically because it respects your privacy.</p>

  <p>Our web host (Netlify) may log IP addresses and basic request metadata in server logs for security purposes. These logs are rotated regularly.</p>

  <h3>Affiliate Links and Outbound Redirects</h3>
  <p>Some links on ChevyRoots are affiliate links. When you click one, we log the click (slug, retailer, timestamp, country, referring page) so we can understand which guides are helpful. We do not associate these clicks with your identity.</p>

  <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Newsletter delivery</strong> — Your email goes to our newsletter provider (Loops.so) to send the weekly digest. You can unsubscribe anytime from any email.</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial operations</strong> — Build submissions and reviews are processed by our editorial team (Crystal, Dave, and trusted moderators).</li>
    <li><strong>Site improvement</strong> — Aggregate analytics help us decide what to write next.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate tracking</strong> — To track which guides convert and improve our recommendations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We don't sell your data to anyone.</li>
    <li>We don't run third-party tracking pixels.</li>
    <li>We don't use Google Analytics or Facebook Pixel.</li>
    <li>We don't email you without your permission.</li>
    <li>We don't share your build submission photos outside of ChevyRoots without your explicit consent.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>ChevyRoots uses a minimal number of cookies, only for basic site functionality (remembering if you've dismissed an announcement, for example). We do not use advertising or tracking cookies.</p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You can request a copy of any personal data we hold about you, correct it, or ask us to delete it entirely. Email <a href="mailto:hello@chevyroots.com">hello@chevyroots.com</a> and we'll handle it within 30 days.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>ChevyRoots is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with information, please contact us so we can delete it.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>If we change this policy, we'll update the "last updated" date at the top and — for material changes — mention it in the newsletter.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@chevyroots.com">hello@chevyroots.com</a>.</p>
</StaticPage>
